      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Hard to go past QUAFFTIDE (3) who is racing in great heart. Had first look here last time and after getting back swept home to score in a Class 3. Up a notch but one of the few in form and looks hard to hold off again. OBVIOUSLY GOOD (1) was fourth here this class but over a sharper trip two back then kept coming over 1350m on the Devonport Synthetic latest. Should be winding up strongly again. BERSERKER (2) has been racing well without winning, the latest a close-up third to Qufftide last time. Draws the inside and should feature again. The race drops away outside those three. CARNELIAN ROCK (4) has a fair record course and distance and is sure to be thereabouts. PURR SEFANEE (9) is fitter for one run back over a sharper trip and can take catching this journey.",
